U||LVIII. THE GREAT LONGING.
U||O my soul, I have taught thee to say ‚Äúto-day‚Äù as ‚Äúonce on a time‚Äù and ‚Äúformerly,‚Äù and to dance thy measure over every Here and There and Yonder.
