U||‚ÄîTowards the golden marvel, the spontaneous bark, and its master: he, however, is the vintager who waiteth with the diamond vintage-knife,‚Äî
U||‚ÄîThy great deliverer, O my soul, the nameless one‚Äîfor whom future songs only will find names! And verily, already hath thy breath the fragrance of future songs,‚Äî
U||‚ÄîAlready glowest thou and dreamest, already drinkest thou thirstily at all deep echoing wells of consolation, already reposeth thy melancholy in the bliss of future songs!‚Äî
U||O my soul, now have I given thee all, and even my last possession, and all my hands have become empty by thee:‚ÄîTHAT I BADE THEE SING, behold, that was my last thing to give!
