U||Then did Life answer me thus, and kept thereby her fine ears closed:
U||‚ÄúO Zarathustra! Crack not so terribly with thy whip! Thou knowest surely that noise killeth thought,‚Äîand just now there came to me such delicate thoughts.
U||We are both of us genuine ne‚Äôer-do-wells and ne‚Äôer-do-ills. Beyond good and evil found we our island and our green meadow‚Äîwe two alone! Therefore must we be friendly to each other!
U||And even should we not love each other from the bottom of our hearts,‚Äîmust we then have a grudge against each other if we do not love each other perfectly?
